article.headline: Navy 70, Lehigh 65
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Trey Stanton scored 16 points and Navy withstood a furious comeback for a 70-65 victory over Lehigh on Wednesday night. Kaleo Kina scored 15 points and Greg Sprink added 10 points for Navy (12-12, 2-7 Patriot League), which snapped Lehigh's seven-game home winning streak against conference opponents. Jose Olivero scored 24 points, Bryan White 18, and Marquis Hall 13 for Lehigh (10-15, 5-4) Navy held a 17-point lead with 13:14 remaining before Lehigh started its comeback try. Lehigh went on a 17-5 run, keyed by a pair of 3-pointers by Olivero, and closed within five points with 8:39 left. responded however with a 17-5 run, keyed by two three-pointers from Olivero, which brought the Brown and White to within five at the 8:39 mark. Bryan White hit a free throw with 5:05 left to pull Lehigh within 61-58, but Navy pulled away and preserved the victory.
